          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:ca0d6a6f1fc5b8989067b9cb8c910950f9096e8de5220788fcd82fa393f173ab",
          "at": "2026-06-25T00:58:34Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "IN-01 says the batch commits as soon as any layer's cumulative diff reaches the per-scope ceiling, but CN-01/AC-03 later say a layer may be at the ceiling and still continue adding tasks from other layers; the split is only required when the next task would make some layer exceed its ceiling. This leaves the plan with conflicting batch-boundary semantics and can make T005 implement an unnecessarily early split, reducing the intended round aggregation.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/feature-batch-default-inversion-2026-06-24/spec.json",
              "line": 51,
              "category": "contradiction"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:ca0d6a6f1fc5b8989067b9cb8c910950f9096e8de5220788fcd82fa393f173ab",
          "at": "2026-06-25T01:03:06Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "AC-04 requires the ceiling values to be adjustable by changing `.harness/config/review-scope.json` only, but its coverage maps solely to T002, which only adds/configures the JSON fields. The runtime pieces that make the setting effective are T003 (`ReviewScopeConfig` stores/returns the effective ceiling) and T004 (loader reads the JSON fields), so the coverage/rendered task list lets AC-04 be considered satisfied without the loader/domain support that the acceptance criterion itself requires.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/feature-batch-default-inversion-2026-06-24/task-coverage.json",
              "line": 30,
              "category": "contradiction"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:096b1b64774c568730c9abd031a0c45fe576b06d8d3be3eadc0f785cbdfd198a",
          "at": "2026-06-25T01:09:48Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`diff_ceiling_for_scope` is documented as returning the global default whenever a scope has no per-scope override, but T003 also requires `ScopeName::Other` to always return `None`. With `default_diff_ceiling` set, those two contracts conflict, so the implementation and tests for `Other` cannot satisfy both artifacts. Clarify whether the global default applies only to configured review scopes or whether `Other` should inherit it.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "track/items/feature-batch-default-inversion-2026-06-24/domain-types.json",
              "line": 109,
              "category": "contradiction"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:7320f83ad0bf4e76f9721b2cb0a1f098946a6975edf685f90d1f39b2d0d32ea3",
          "at": "2026-06-25T01:13:14Z"
        },
